{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_02_system_architecture", "label": "System architecture (sense -> understand -> render)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/02-system-architecture.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Three layers: sense -> understand -> render. Laptop (brain) does sense + understand; the hardware chain does render. Documents the full connector chain and brain placement."}, {"id": "docs_02_system_architecture_hardware_chain", "label": "Hardware render chain (laptop -> Vantec -> SK473 -> KHD drivers)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/02-system-architecture.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Laptop --USB data--> 2x Vantec NBA-200U (USB digital -> 8 analog ch each) --3.5mm plug--> 6x SK473 PAM8403 amp boards --18 AWG speaker wire soldered to output pads--> 12x KHD 3 Ohm/5 W drivers (6 back strings + 6 torso fret-zones)."}, {"id": "docs_02_system_architecture_connector_isolation", "label": "Connector cheat-sheet + bounded power isolation", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/02-system-architecture.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The amp is the translator: 3.5 mm line-level in -> amplified power out on bare wire. Bare wire never touches the Vantec. The 3.5 mm cable shares signal ground but carries only line-level current and the amp's 5 V rail is isolated, so amp power cannot flow back into the laptop \u2014 bounded isolation, not total absence of any DC path."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_02_system_architecture", "target": "docs_02_system_architecture_hardware_chain", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/02-system-architecture.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_02_system_architecture"